The paper deals with fair allocation, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The proposed assumption on the underlying cardinal utilities of the players is related to decision-making and preference modeling, which are also topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents a polynomial-time algorithm, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the simulations and experiments conducted in the paper involve statistical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
